  "informal_statement": "For every real x ≥ 2, ∫_2^x (log t + 1) · log(t + 2)/(t² log² t) dt ≤ 1 + 1/log 2.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Bound log(t+2) against t^(1/2)-free elementary comparisons so the integrand is dominated by a multiple of the exactly integrable weight kernel; integrate the dominating kernel in closed form and evaluate the constant.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem mertens_error_integral_log_bound :\n    ∀ x : ℝ, 2 ≤ x →\n      (∫ t in (2:ℝ)..x, (Real.log t + 1) * Real.log (t + 2) / (t^2 * (Real.log t)^2))\n        ≤ 1 + (Real.log 2)⁻¹",
